Prostomium slightly as wide as long, anterior margin truncate, lateral margins rounded, posterior margin with a shallow notch, 1/5 as long as prostomium (
Fig. 37B
). Antennae digitate, 4-5 times as long as wide, or longer than interocular distance. Eyes brownish, anterior ones twice as large as posterior ones.

Parapodia (dissected from 
paratypes
) with chaetal lobes tapered, truncate (
Fig. 37C
); dorsal cirri with cirrophores about twice as long as wide, cirrostyle basally cylindrical, smooth, articulated throughout most of its length, longer than body width (including parapodia); ventral cirri irregulary contracted, few complete, reaching chaetal tips.

Neurochaetae about 20 per bundle, blades bidentate, 3-4 times as long as wide; blades aligned at a certain angle from handle, teeth of similar length, subdistal tooth usually wider, guard thick, approaching subdistal tooth (
Fig. 37D
).

Posterior region tapered into a blunt cone (
Fig. 37E
); pygidium rugose, anus with seven low, blunt triangular papillae.
